The seventh-seeded Anderson defeated Argentina’s Nicolas Kicker 7-6 (7/1), 7-6 (7/3) on Monday to reach the fourth round. This followed Anderson’s 7-5, 6-4 win over Russia’s Evgeny Donskoy over the weekend. Anderson will next face 11th-seeded Pablo Carreno Busta from Spain. Anderson holds a 3-0 head-to-head record against the Spaniard, including a four-sets victory in their most recent meeting at last year’s US Open. --news24--